## In Scope
- perform necessary adjustments in start.S to move the .data section to RAM
    - the .data section is built into the firmware image hex file, during compilation. Since it corresponds to globally initialized variables, it must copied to the RAM. 
- Creation of firmware functions to receive on the serial port
- Function to check character availability in the buffer
- Integration test: replace the infinite loop "> alive" with a simple command that responds "alive"
- Update the architecture documents, accordingly to the new feature(current-architecture.md, hw-sw-contract.md, repository-map.md)
- This feature requires an update to the hw-sw-contract.md due to UART register reorganization.

